==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Opprobrium
<hw>Op*pro"bri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>) + <ets>probrum</ets> reproach,
disgrace.]</ety> <def>A state of disgrace; infamy; reproach mingled with
contempt; odium{3}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source><source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Abusive language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Being both dramatic author and dramatic performer, he found
himself heir to a twofold <qex>opprobrium</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Opprobry</ent>⟦br⟧
